            <h2>The Long-Term Yield Compression</h2>
            <p>The historical dividend yield of the S&P 500 has undergone a massive transformation. For decades prior to the 1990s, income investors could reliably expect 3% to 5% yields from large-cap equities. Today, the yield routinely hovers just above 1%.</p>
            <p>This interactive chart compares the S&P 500 dividend yield history against the 10-year Treasury yield, providing context on how stock yields measure up to the "risk-free" rate.</p>

